The Pistons celebrate their 2004 NBA championship after ousting the Los Angeles Lakers.
The Pistons would go on to win the series in Game 6 to head to the NBA Finals.
► June 3, 1990 – Pistons 93, Bulls 74: The Pistons beat back the Bulls in the Eastern Conference finals for a second straight year.
The Pistons' Tayshaun Prince (22) blocks the shot of Pacers guard Reggie Miller (31) late in Game 2 of the 2004 Eastern Conference finals in Indianapolis.
► June 14, 2004 – Pistons 100, Lakers 87: The 2004 Lakers had a half-dozen Hall of Famers on their bench, including two coaches.